public class EdgeDetClass
extends com.mathworks.toolbox.javabuilder.internal.MWComponentInstance<EdgeDetClass>

The EdgeDetClass class provides a Java interface to the M-functions from the files: 

  C:\\MatlabWorks\\EdgeDetection.m
The dispose() method must be called on a EdgeDetClass instance when it is no longer needed to ensure that native resources allocated by this class are properly freed.

EdgeDetection

public void EdgeDetection(java.util.List lhs,
                          java.util.List rhs)
                   throws com.mathworks.toolbox.javabuilder.MWException
Provides the interface for calling the EdgeDetection M-function where the first input, an instance of List, receives the output of the M-function and the second input, also an instance of List, provides the input to the M-function.

M-documentation as provided by the author of the M function: 

 % GelenImage='C:/kiz.jpg';
 % AlgoritmaTip='prewit';
 % Threshold='Manuel';
 % t=0.01;
 % ScanType ='vertical';
 % KayitYeri='c:/ist.jpg';

Parameters:
lhs - List in which to return outputs. Number of outputs (nargout) is determined by allocated size of this List. Outputs are returned as sub-classes of com.mathworks.toolbox.javabuilder.MWArray. Each output array should be freed by calling its dispose() method.
rhs - List containing inputs. Number of inputs (nargin) is determined by the allocated size of this List. Input arguments may be passed as sub-classes of com.mathworks.toolbox.javabuilder.MWArray, or as arrays of any supported Java type. Arguments passed as Java types are converted to MATLAB arrays according to default conversion rules.
Throws:
com.mathworks.toolbox.javabuilder.MWException - An error has occurred during the function call.

EdgeDetection

public java.lang.Object[] EdgeDetection(java.lang.Object... rhs)
                                 throws com.mathworks.toolbox.javabuilder.MWException
Provides the standard interface for calling the EdgeDetection M-function with 6 input arguments. Input arguments may be passed as sub-classes of com.mathworks.toolbox.javabuilder.MWArray, or as arrays of any supported Java type. Arguments passed as Java types are converted to MATLAB arrays according to default conversion rules.

M-documentation as provided by the author of the M function: 

 % GelenImage='C:/kiz.jpg';
 % AlgoritmaTip='prewit';
 % Threshold='Manuel';
 % t=0.01;
 % ScanType ='vertical';
 % KayitYeri='c:/ist.jpg';

Parameters:
rhs - The inputs to the M function.
Returns:
Array of length nargout containing the function outputs. Outputs are returned as sub-classes of com.mathworks.toolbox.javabuilder.MWArray. Each output array should be freed by calling its dispose() method.
Throws:
com.mathworks.toolbox.javabuilder.MWException - An error has occurred during the function call.
